# Headroom — mandatory token savings (all agents)

**Every agent, subagent, and background task in this repo must follow these rules.** Token waste is never acceptable.

---

## 1. Prefix every CLI command with `rtk`

`rtk` (Rust Token Killer) strips noise from command output before it reaches the LLM — **60–90% fewer tokens, zero behaviour change**. If `rtk` has no filter for a command it passes through unchanged, so it is always safe.

```bash
# Git
rtk git status          rtk git diff            rtk git log

# Files & search
rtk ls <path>           rtk read <file>         rtk grep <pattern>
rtk find <pattern>      rtk diff <file>

# Tests — shows failures only (90–99% savings)
rtk npm run test        rtk pytest tests/

# Build & lint — shows errors only (80–90% savings)
rtk npm run lint        rtk tsc                 rtk npx tsc --noEmit
rtk prettier --check    rtk ruff check

# GitHub
rtk gh pr view <n>      rtk gh run list         rtk gh issue list

# Package managers
rtk npm install         rtk npm run <script>    rtk pip list
```

**Command chains:** prefix each segment — `rtk git add . && rtk git commit -m "msg"`  
**Debugging only:** omit `rtk` when you need raw unfiltered output.

---

## 2. Use `headroom_compress` MCP tool for large content

Before sending any large block of text to the model (RAG results, log files, long file reads, tool outputs > ~500 lines), call the `headroom_compress` MCP tool:

```
headroom_compress(content="<large text>")
```

This compresses the content in-place and caches the original for retrieval on demand — typically **70–95% token reduction**.

---

## 3. Session startup

At the start of every session, run from the **Flip repo root**:

```bash
headroom wrap cursor
```

This starts the Headroom proxy on `http://127.0.0.1:8787` and refreshes the `.cursorrules` RTK instructions.

**One-time setup** (if `rtk` or `headroom` is missing):
```bash
pip install "headroom-ai[proxy,mcp]"
headroom wrap cursor
```

**Configure Cursor** — after the proxy is running, set in **Settings → Models**:

| Model family | Base URL override |
|---|---|
| OpenAI | `http://127.0.0.1:8787/p/Flip/v1` |
| Anthropic | `http://127.0.0.1:8787/p/Flip` |

---

## 4. Applies to all rules and agents

This rule takes precedence over any other rule that does not mention token savings. All other `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files inherit this requirement. Parallel subagents launched by `auto-parallel-work.mdc` must each independently apply the `rtk` prefix and `headroom_compress` tool.
